      "properties": {
        "name": "Leo"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:f93f6ce3ae3b3f94",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 161,
        "char_start": 5,
        "episode_id": "09ead36d-954f-5cbb-ae3f-6f0d5985233d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Welcome back to Frame & Light. Today we're talking about underwater photography, and I'm joined by Ava, underwater photographer. Ava, thanks for being here.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 6000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 0,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-02",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Ava"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:3c678d272fa18881",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 266,
        "char_start": 167,
        "episode_id": "09ead36d-954f-5cbb-ae3f-6f0d5985233d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Thanks, Leo. Excited for this one \u2014 underwater imaging is something I've been thinking about a lot.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 12000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 6000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:613c813e9ad906a6",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 421,
        "char_start": 272,
        "episode_id": "09ead36d-954f-5cbb-ae3f-6f0d5985233d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Today's episode is sponsored by Adobe. Adobe Creative Cloud puts Lightroom, Photoshop, and Premiere on every device you edit on. Try adobe.com today.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:fa18c3bb338e30f1",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 503,
        "char_start": 421,
        "episode_id": "09ead36d-954f-5cbb-ae3f-6f0d5985233d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "I want to dig into that. What's the version of the question that actually matters?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:da1d520c423a3e72",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 730,
        "char_start": 509,
        "episode_id": "09ead36d-954f-5cbb-ae3f-6f0d5985233d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "I'd put it this way: An underwater frame is built around backscatter management before it's about composition. We've seen this play out at teams using Capture One. And the second-order effect is the part most people miss.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:a2dc9e1c4f362c2a",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 829,
        "char_start": 736,
        "episode_id": "09ead36d-954f-5cbb-ae3f-6f0d5985233d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "How do you balance that? What's something you used to believe about this that you've revised?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p04_e01.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
